linkedList.list

Class BasicList<N extends ListNode<T>,T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • linkedList.list.BasicList<N,T>
  • Type Parameters:
    N - the type of node used in this list (for example, single or double linked)
    T - the type of object stored in this list
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    LinkedList<N,T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DoubleLinkQueue, SingleLinkStack

    public abstract class BasicList<N extends ListNode<T>,T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements LinkedList<N,T>
    Minimal implementation of list objects. Defines the root node, access methods, and test for emptiness.
    Version:
    October 2019
    Author:
    Hugh Osborne
